# Tech Stack

## Frontend
- React 19 + TypeScript, built with Vite
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 + a shadcn-style component system
  (`components.json`, `class-variance-authority`, `tailwind-merge`)
- Charts: `recharts`
- Testing: `vitest` (business logic only — see `current-status.md`)

## Backend
- FastAPI (Python)
- Data validation/modeling: Pydantic (`BaseModel`, `Literal` types)
- No database — data is generated in-memory per request
  (`generate_mock_movements`, seeded for consistency)
- Testing: `pytest` + FastAPI's `TestClient`

## Infrastructure / Tooling
- Docker Compose orchestrates two services: `frontend` (port 5173)
  and `backend` (port 8000, plus 5678 for remote debugging via
  `debugpy`)
- Frontend calls the backend via `VITE_API_BASE_URL` (falls back to
  same-origin if unset)

## Key dependencies worth knowing
- `backend/requirements.txt` is currently unpinned and doesn't
  separate dev tools from runtime deps (`fastapi`, `debugpy`, `pytest`
  all listed together) — flagged in `.agents/rules/environment-boundary.md`
- Frontend dependency versions are pinned normally via
  `package-lock.json`, unlike the backend